Assets.Name: the_HOMETOWN
Assets.Description:
Hello Everybody !
Here we are for the v1.0 of my most ambitious map !

the_HOMETOWN  is my take on trying to push the custom map idea a bit further.
- You’ll find a story with cinematics, objectives, collectables, interactions and so on...
- This is a first test / draft, so there is a lot of room for improvement.

**DISCLAIMER : 
The plan was to do a full voice over work on this map but due to the fact that I’m not a native english speaker, nor a professional actor, and I didn’t wanted to push the v1 launch I’m putting that on the side.
I know following a story and getting involved with just subtitles and texts is not the best…
I have a solution in mind, but let’s see if you guys think it’s worth it first   :)
...I kept some random voice over I did here and there, just to give an idea.**

the STORY :

You’re playing the KID, a skate prodigy that was slowly becoming a legend before his terrible choices and mistakes made him lose everything.
On his road to redemption, he needs to go back to his birthplace, while his past is haunting him.

Chapter 1 : the old factory is where the KID learnt everything. An abandoned place where he created his first spots, and where he hid something truly special. 
This chapter represent weeks of work (between 10pm and 1am due to my real job and family with a baby life haha).
I had tons of fun doing it, and I hope you’ll have some as well  :)

It should keep you occupied (hopefully) for a solid hour or two for the 100%
Thanks -


***Direct DL :  

p.s - PLEASE !!  send me your links with Live / Replays / Gifs, I would LOVE to see you play the map.
```css
Exit the map (use the door) at the end of the story to get a nice bonus...
``````diff
- Current build :  v1.0.1
cleaning of some penetrating objects 
cleaning of the glitch between the start door and the wall
you can now skip the intro by pressing ‘N’
```

Assets.Name: PortHarbor
Assets.Description:
Hey everyone!  👋     I finally finished Port Harbor after all this time. This is actually my second map. I built this before ING Park, but had to fix things because of that update we all know about by now. So without further ado. 

  PORT HARBOR
  
  With the Mt. Valley authorities instructing the demolition of The Establishment, the areas skateboarders were left to roam the streets. Rand from INGcorperated stepped in and opened up his training facility ING Park and looked like a public savior in the process. Having watched his rival score politcal points, Weeland Skeeter owner of Skeeter Construction vowed to take the politics out of the areas skatboarding scene... and boy did he make a statement with how. 

 The deed to port Harbor changed hands between INGcorperated and Skeeter Construction 20 years ago in a back alley game of S.K.A.T.E. where Weeland defeated Rand with a Nollie Hardflip to One Wheel Nose Manual across the top of a flat bar. It was Weelands last big win before his accident. With Rand opening ING Park and the Mt.Valley athorites demolishing The Establishment for safety reasons, Weeland has stepped in to help keep the cities politics out of skateboarding.

Assets.Name: DIY_01_SciLab
Assets.Description:
DIY 01 Science Laboratory

  For the first installment in the DIY Playground Collection I used the Science Laboratory environment pack.  Inspired by the 7 stair ledge set up and the Greenhouse style glass windows offered in the pack I set off to get the basics of the Collection down.  The Large curved desk in the middle of the room should be a great center piece to build on and around. With multiple level changes around the room it should be a good place to start building that DIY park you know you always wanted. All areas in this map are accessible with no added ramps, but that will change in future maps. Before you ask, NO the glass half pipe in the observatory room is NOT skateable.  Though we all wish it was, it has giant gaps between the glass panels and that would need more changes outside of the pack. Which is moving away from the quick in pack only idea of the collection.  I also plan to add baked indoor lighting when I learn it better so we can have stars shining in the roof.   

  THANK YOU TO ALL IN THE SESSION COMMUNITY!
